						               													<description>Why did Oskar climb into a garbage can freshly showered? Why did Mrs. &amp;Ouml;hmchen serve her burglar coffee and cake? Why was Tiago mistaken for a turkey? And how could the toilet flush expose a thief?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These funny and absurd riddles about disgusting ice creams, burning underpants, clumsy criminals or exploding dog poop are all a bit curious - and sometimes sheer unbelievable. The squeaky-clean puzzle stories are full of wit and can only be solved by clever thinking around corners and good deduction skills. Disbelief and spontaneous smiles included!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The black stories Junior are exciting puzzle stories on cards, which must be cracked together. Only the game leader knows the solution to the riddle because he reads the riddle on the front aloud and may also study the solution on the back carefully. The other players now try to find the solution step by step by asking questions and guessing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
